      "content": "For dress codes, the baseline is conservative tailoring—think dark, well-fitting suits for men and elegant, structured attire for women, avoiding anything overly flashy. In dining, the standard involves mindful pacing, proper utensil use, and never speaking with a full mouth, showing restraint. During meetings, sophisticated communication means speaking clearly, concisely, and listening actively before responding, rather than dominating the conversation with volume or jargon. These practices signal discipline and respect, which are universally valued traits.",
